 y = f(x)= 2x^2+3x-2
\begin{align}f(x) &= 2x^2 + 3x - 2 \\                     &= 2\left(x^2+\frac{3}{2}x\right) -2 \\                     &= 2\left(x^2+\frac{3}{2}x+\frac{9}{16}-\frac{9}{16}\right) -2\\                     &= 2\left(x^2 +\frac{3}{2}x+\frac{9}{16}\right) -2\left(\frac{9}{16}\right)-2\\                     &= 2\left(x+\frac{3}{4}\right)^2 - \frac{25}{8}\end{align}
